\q1 вүҲandВҰ300207 who has Yahweh's \add вүҲpower\add* been revealedВҰ300212 to?
\q1
\v 2 He grew in front of him like a youngВҰ300215 plantВҰ300215,
\q1 вүҲand like a root out of the dry groundВҰ300218.
\q1 He had no \add fancy\add* form or splendourВҰ300225 to lookВҰ300226 at,
\q1 вүҲand his appearanceВҰ300229 \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ300220 attract us to him\add*.
\q1
\v 3 He was despised and rejectedВҰ300233 by peopleвҖ”
\q1 вүҲa manВҰ300235 \add вүҲwith a lot of\add* pain and familiar with sicknessВҰ300238
\q1 like someone that \add вүҲmost people would look away from\add*
\q1 вүҲand despise him, \add вүҲrather than to\add* esteemВҰ300244 him.
\b
\q1
\v 4 \add вүҲDespite that\add*, he's borne our sicknessesВҰ300247
\q1 вүҲand carriedВҰ300251 our sorrowsВҰ300250.
\q1 We \add вүҲthought\add* that he'd been struckВҰ300255 down by GodВҰ300256вҖ”
\q1 вүҲattacked and made to suffer.\x + \xo 53:4: \xt Mat 8:17.\x*
\q1
\v 5 \add вүҲButВҰ300259\add* he was piercedВҰ300260 for our disobedience,
\q1 вүҲand crushedВҰ300262 for our wicked actions.
\q1 The punishment that \add gave us\add* peaceВҰ300265 was onВҰ300267 him,
\q1 вүҲand we were healedВҰ300268 \add thanks\add* to his woundsВҰ300267.\x + \xo 53:5: \xt 1Pe 2:24.\x*
\q1
\v 6 We've all strayed away like sheepВҰ300273вҖ”
\q1 вүҲ\add вүҲeveryone's gone in their own direction\add*
\q1 andВҰ300278 YahwehВҰ300278 has placed all ourВҰ300283 disobedience onto him.\x + \xo 53:6: \xt 1Pe 2:25.\x*
\b
\q1
\v 7 He was oppressedВҰ300285 and tormented
\q1 \add вүҲbutВҰ300286\add* like a lamb being led away to be slaughteredВҰ300293, he didn't open his mouth,
\q1 вүҲand like a sheepВҰ300295 that's silent in frontВҰ300296 of its shearersВҰ300297, he didn't open his mouth.\x + \xo 53:7: \xt Rev 5:6.\x*
\q1
\v 8 \add вүҲAfter\add* oppressionВҰ300303 and judgementВҰ300304, he was takenВҰ300305 away,
\q1 \add вүҲbutВҰ300304 how many of his peers even cared\add* that he was cut off from the land of the livingВҰ300314?
\q1 He was woundedВҰ300317 because of the disobedience of my peopleВҰ300316.
\q1
\v 9 His burial place was among the criminals,
\q1 and a rich man atВҰ300328 his deathВҰ300328,
\q1 although he'd committed no violentВҰ300332 acts,
\q1 and \add вүҲhad never spoken deceitfullyВҰ300335\add*.\x + \xo 53:9: \xt 1Pe 2:22.\x*
\b
\q1
\v 10 \add вүҲButВҰ300338\add* YahwehВҰ300352 desiredВҰ300339 to crushВҰ300340 himвҖ”
\q1 he made him sickВҰ300341 if it would make his lifeВҰ300346 a guilt-offering.
\q1 He will live long and seeВҰ300347 offspringВҰ300348,
\q1 and Yahweh' plans will prosperВҰ300354 \add вүҲthrough his work\add*.
\q1
\v 11 Due to his internal anguishВҰ300356, he'll be able to seeВҰ300358.
\q1 He'll be satisfiedВҰ300359 withВҰ300360 his knowledgeВҰ300360.
\q1 My \add вүҲobedient\add* servantВҰ300363 will justifyВҰ300361 many,
\q1 and he will carryВҰ300367 theirВҰ300365 disobedience.
\q1
\v 12 \add вүҲBecause of that,\add* I'll allocate a portionВҰ300370 for him.
\q1 He'll divide out the plunderВҰ300378 to a powerful people
\q1 becauseВҰ300379 he pouredВҰ300381 out his lifeВҰ300383 \add вүҲresulting inВҰ300373\add* his deathВҰ300382.
\q1 He was included withВҰ300373 the wicked,
\q1 and he bore the disobedience of many people,
\q1 and he intervened onВҰ300373 behalf of the disobedient.\x + \xo 53:12: \xt Luk 22:37.\x*
